</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8E2EE4A7534A3C23DB8D38F88D7C2F4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="comparisons">
<paragraph id="D70D82BAB4E739D056C25A80D2A7582F" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Comparisons.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F85503F7E2C6E84F85828B2527B682F" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
The general body shape, color, and prolongation of the third dorsal-fin spine in 
<taxonomicName id="1DFA34A01D4871B64D6DBF866B6FB956" authorityName="Shepherd &amp; Phelps &amp; Pinheiro &amp; Rocha &amp; Rocha" authorityYear="2020" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Plectranthias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectranthias polygonius" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polygonius">
<emphasis id="B5F0D1C141AD18E323446A24847A3F08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Plectranthias polygonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. resemble 
<taxonomicName id="8D8ADC2C5F4334728FCC7ED77462568E" genus="P." lsidName="P. inermis" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="90807E6639C34E666ED44E3058754339" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C5586DE894840174FFF7BDF3409205" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="A2507B641AE710DCCB469827DA7B1627" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F7524B10A96F9A712BCE00DB11BD523A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Plectranthias polygonius sp. nov. at Erikub Atoll, Republic of the Marshall Islands, at a depth of 120 m (A), aquarium photos of P. inermis (B), and P. altipinnatus (C). Photographs by LA Rocha (A) and YK Tea (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.941.50243.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/421775" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">2B, C</figureCitation>
); however, the barcode fragment of the COI gene of 
<taxonomicName id="8BC83528E5411343A7BA9CA06EF59305" genus="P." lsidName="P. polygonius" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="polygonius">
<emphasis id="72A2D4B09CD5E7B828D5985C21B10D4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. polygonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is not close to any published barcode sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="6A01CDDDE9C067EF2E8DDFA8E8A0D0FA" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1873" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Plectranthias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectranthias" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="792C84A92DF807AE893F388E29D358A3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Plectranthias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with approximately 15% uncorrected pairwise genetic distance from several species in the genus. Morphologically, it can easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="529447BDEB6836C91BFE6F458CFBCC3B" genus="P." lsidName="P. inermis" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="3658A8D5583A01E327973D35140D8023" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having ten circumpeduncular scales (vs. 14 or 15 in 
<taxonomicName id="A235153E261C6DD7214840EA6F66E254" genus="P." lsidName="P. inermis" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="203C70AB77E360CEFF27605CDE3DDF59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); canine teeth on the lower jaw (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="6CA0B1AEA9B737954373A6C548FA927B" genus="P." lsidName="P. inermis" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="93AA83B0FE75BF98EF4312868DE3FF59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and 14-17 spines on the posterior edge of the preopercle (spines lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="CDA72D04CA9D0DCE63A36F567AFD2DB7" genus="P." lsidName="P. inermis" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="584BA857571B090E14825E2EB0CC29C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; feebly serrated in 
<taxonomicName id="7B64A9EA890EA762036FF7C14ACD3BBE" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="491A3023731E2BFC3FD352C085BB8096" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="9647EE024944B75ECB8F3E27C19FD925" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="952909A340C291FC39DDF4B7C6DECFEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having X, 16 dorsal-fin rays (X, 18 in 
<taxonomicName id="461E3B27A08A9D0DAF82CD0FF1371695" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="2D6FFB77971A674A0373E6C1394E4128" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a shallower body (3.2-3.4 in SL vs. 2.8 in 
<taxonomicName id="A41CF1AEB752850A2E3DFFC41D9DD8F8" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="DF91885216E9339592F44BE181846EBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), smaller head (3.1-3.2 in SL vs. 2.2 in 
<taxonomicName id="71E97BA9C0587B4F2FD01FB94BE0BAAF" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="9DAAFBFB807743D08EBB6291BCD45932" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and a larger eye (2.8 in HL vs. 4.75 in 
<taxonomicName id="1DA9012904B3EE4C0013DAE8B5C96DC2" genus="P." lsidName="P. altipinnatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="altipinnatus">
<emphasis id="73162150FE6C6505848A58E15FEABD16" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">P. altipinnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
